cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.NE. 

The paper describes a question answering system that uses neural network models and information retrieval models, which are commonly used in natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also uses supervised machine learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Information retrieval models are commonly used in search engines, which fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of neural network models falls under cs.LG (Learning), and the combination of different models falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
